    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Phylum that includes common vertebrates such as fishes, amphibians, reptiles, birds, mammals, as well as the tunicates and lancelets. With few exceptions, chordates are active animals with bilaterally symmetric bodies that are longitudinally differentiated into head, trunk, and tail. The most distinctive morphological features of chordates are the notochord, nerve cord, and visceral clefts and arches. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047701/Tree of Life Web Project (1995-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>包括魚類、兩棲類、爬蟲類、鳥類以及哺乳類等常見的脊椎動物門，此外亦包括尾索類與文昌魚。除了少數的脊索動物外，大部分皆極為活躍，身體兩邊對稱，縱向分為頭部、軀幹及尾部。脊索動物的形態特徵當中，最具特色的即為牠們的脊索、神經索、鰓裂以及鰓弓。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stam van gewone gewervelde dieren als vissen, amfibieën, reptielen, vogels, zoogdieren en manteldiertjes en lancetvisjes. Bijna alle chordadieren zijn actieve dieren met bilateraal symmetrische lichamen die in de lengte zijn onderverdeeld in een hoofd, romp en staart. Het belangrijkste morfologische kenmerk van chordadieren zijn de chorda dorsalis (bij embryo's), de wervelkolom en de inwendige holtes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
